title: Launch Roundup – Arianespace launches Ariane 5 final flight; SpaceX to fly one of last Starlink v1.5 flights
summary: Three launches are currently planned for the week of July 2 through July 9. The first one took place on Wednesday, July 5, with a European rocket successfully making its 117th and final flight. Later in the week, SpaceX plans two Falcon 9 flights with Starlink payloads on Friday, July 7 and Sunday, July 9. These three flights will be the 98th, 99th, and 100th orbital launch attempts of 2023, respectively.
